Summary ! : 

Us girlies have a 28 - 34 day hormonal cycle , men have a 24 hour one. 

We have 4 phases ‚ú®‚ú®‚ú®:

1. Menstrual : day 1 - 6 - This phase starts the day you start your period and ends when you end your period) 
2. Follicular üå∏: Day 7 - 13 - this phase starts after you end your period until the day you ovulate. It‚Äôs your Inner spring . Hormones starting to come back and your starting to feel more like yourself üíñ
3. Ovulatory ‚ú®: Day 14- 18 - This starts the day you ovulate and lasts about 6 days. You are going to be feeling your most confident and best self here . All the good hormones at peak here!
4. Luteal phase üçÉ üçÇ: Day 19-28 - This starts after your ovulatory phase and ends when you start you period. Technically has 2 phases to this phase. First half will be feeling great still from all those good hormones from your ovulatory phase and then the second half the week - week 1/2 before you get ur period) your going to start to feel ur hormones dip. Feeling tired and weaker here. 

These are typical days but every one‚Äôs body is different and could be a couple days difference for you individually! 
That‚Äôs why it‚Äôs always a good idea to track ur cycle.

And I want to really preface I‚Äôm not a doctor and this is not perspective in anyway. Just me sharing the information I have learned and trialed and errored over the past year & a half. 

And as always if you‚Äôre needing help to better understand your body and how to specifically apply this info to you, reach out shoot me a DM this is what I do and I‚Äôd love to work with you! 

Alright beauties that‚Äôs it for part 1 ! Check in on ‚ú® Wednesday ‚ú®for part 2 going over your follicular phase and how you can best exercises and eat during that time to make sure you‚Äôre thriving and working with your body not against it üí™ üíñüíñ 
Hope this info helps you better work with your body and helps get you thriving!
